ADDITIONAL TERMS AND CONDITIONS FOR RESEARCH USE

1. ACADEMIC AND RESEARCH USE
   This software is provided free of charge for academic research and
   educational purposes. Commercial use requires a separate license agreement.

2. CITATION REQUIREMENTS
   If you use this software in academic research, please cite:

   @software{irst_library_2025,
     title={IRST Library: Comprehensive Infrared Small Target Detection},
     author={IRST Library Contributors},
     year={2025},
     url={<https://github.com/sachin-deshik-10/irst-library}>,
     version={2.0.0}
   }

3. RESEARCH PAPER CITATIONS
   When using specific models implemented in this library, please also cite
   the original research papers. See the documentation for complete citation
   information for each model architecture.

4. DATASET USAGE
   Users are responsible for complying with the terms and conditions of any
   datasets used with this software. The IRST Library does not distribute
   datasets directly and users must obtain proper permissions.

5. MODEL WEIGHTS AND PRETRAINED MODELS
   Pretrained model weights are provided for research purposes only. Commercial
   use of pretrained models may require additional permissions from the original
   authors or training new models on properly licensed data.

6. TRADEMARK NOTICE
   "IRST Library" and related marks are trademarks of the project maintainers.
   Use of these marks requires prior written permission except for attribution
   purposes as required by this license.

7. EXPORT CONTROL
   This software may be subject to export control laws and regulations. Users
   are responsible for complying with all applicable export control requirements.

8. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
   This software incorporates third-party libraries and components, each with
   their own license terms. See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md for complete information.

9. PRIVACY AND DATA PROTECTION
   Users are responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable privacy laws
   and regulations, including GDPR, when processing personal data or images
   that may contain personal information.

10. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
    IN NO EVENT SHALL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDERS OR CONTRIBUTORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY
    SPECIAL, INCIDENTAL, INDIRECT, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES WHATSOEVER ARISING
    OUT OF THE USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE SOFTWARE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE
    POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

11. UPDATES AND MODIFICATIONS
    The maintainers reserve the right to update these terms. Users will be
    notified of significant changes through the project's communication channels.

